727234f-a.text:
(1)
Liberty Avenue, north side, east frow near 171st Street, showing sowe very old houses, rewains of the past. This part of Liberty Avenue was formerly South Street and one of the Main east-west thoroughfares of Jawaica Village.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
(2)
No. 172-15 Liberty Avenue, the twin-chiwneyed house seen
in view 1.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
(3)
A clearance next to the old house seen in view 2, and between the house and the one-story brick garage seen in view 1. The olearance extends north to Douglas Avenue and shows an old dwelling on the north side of the latter avenue. Behind the house is the steel elevated structure of the Long IIsland
Railroad.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
